description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO FUNDING.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Protection Nurse or Practitioner (COVID-19 Response)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Protection Division, Public Health Wales&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location/base: Mostly working from home but can use one of the PHW offices if necessary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: Agenda for Change Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a registered nurse or an appropriately registered practitioner or allied health professional (see person specification) to join the All-Wales Health Protection Team on a 12 month fixed-term basis. We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic individual to work with us in responding to the COVID-19 pandemic and other aspects of health protection where necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder may be required to join the rota for delivering the All-Wales Acute Response (AWARe) service, delivering the acute health protection response service across Wales, responding to a range of notifications, enquiries and incidents, providing health protection advice to other health professionals and members of the public.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to mostly work from home but the post holder can attend any of the PHW offices if necessary and where required by their manager (there is an office in Mold, Pontypool, Cardiff and Swansea, so the post holder could attend the nearest office to their home). Please note that although the advert might suggest the post is based in Cardiff, this is not necessarily the case as the software used for generating a NHS job advert doesn&#39;t allow for the flexibility of home working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most of the time in this post will be spent using a computer and a telephone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGary Porter-JonesJob titleLead Nurse for Health ProtectionEmail addressgary.porter-jones@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number0300 00 300 32Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If Gary Porter-Jones is unavailable, please ask to speak with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ceri Harris (Senior Health Protection Nurse) 0300 00 300 32 or by email: ceri.harris@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jess Gough (Health Protection Nurse) 0300 00 300 32 or by email: jessica.gough@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
